r"""
Time-cutoff / empty-truth patch for simple_sim_cont_time_gruode.py
==================================================================

SYMPTOM
    IndexError: index 0 is out of bounds for axis 0 with size 0
    at  firm_track_time = truth_states_sr_cut[0][0]

ROOT CAUSE
    sim_ingress() filters truth rows with a HARD-CODED absolute-time ceiling:

        truth_states_sr_cut = np.asarray(
            tuple(x for x in truth_states
                  if x[TIME_INDEX] < 122.0 and not np.allclose(x[VEL_SLICE], [0,0,0])),
            dtype=np.float64,
        )

    That 122.0 s ceiling assumes trajectories that START near t=0 (full/boost-
    inclusive). The phase library's glide files are PRE-SEGMENTED to the glide
    portion, which begins deep into flight -- e.g. Albuqurque_lp10 runs
    t=439..752 s. Every row is > 122, so the filter empties the array and the
    next line indexes [0] on nothing.

    The same 122.0 ceiling is also used as the extrapolation stop condition in
    NEXT_extrapolation ("while temp_iter < n_steps and float(validity_time) <
    122.0"), which would stop a glide extrap immediately for the same reason.

FIX
    Replace the absolute ceiling with one anchored to the file's own start
    time, exposed as a CLI arg so nothing is silently hard-coded. Default
    behavior for glide is "no early time cut" (the velocity!=0 filter and the
    slant-range / ground checks already bound the trajectory). Also add an
    empty-array guard so a genuinely empty file is skipped, matching the
    existing (-1,-1,-1) "bad file" sentinel that sim_single_truth handles.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
APPLY THESE THREE EDITS to simple_sim_cont_time_gruode.py
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
"""

